#import "../../lib.typ": prologue

#prologue("Narumi Mona wants to change")[
  I threw my phone at the bed, before diving head-first into my pillow.

  These days had been exhausting, to say the least. Far beyond my wildest
  imagination.

  I had thought I would spend my high school days like how my middle school
  experience went: no one particularly close, yet not isolated enough to be
  called a loner. Now, I was surrounded by people at any opportunity, and this
  probably sounds self-centered, but I think I _might_ be the most popular girl
  in class.

  And with great power comes great responsibility. The human interaction I had
  to do for the whole day drained every ounce of my social battery. I was
  fatigued to the point that scrolling social media on my phone would feel as if
  running laps around the house. I just wanted to fall asleep right now.

  Yet, my newfound popularity was not the most unexpected thing that happened
  in the last three days.

  What really surprised me was my two new friends, Nanba Mikoto and Kazugai Uta.

  They initially reached out to me with the same reason as everyone else:
  wanting to confirm whether I was Narumi Sena's little sister or not. I was not
  really expecting much from them, until...

  "May I ask, Narumi-san, are you, by any chance, interested in idols?"

  I could still recall that moment clearly. I was going with the flow, rambling
  all sorts of nonsense about the life of us sisters, until Mikoto gave that
  sudden question and everyone went silent.

  I was shocked that the world "idol" even entered the conversation, and was so
  worried about me slipping up something that could potentially tarnish my high
  school life in ruins, yet I answered her question honestly.

  It was the moment I gambled everything on, and fortunately, my bet paid off in
  the end. Uta and Mikoto turned out to be idol fans like me, albeit seemingly
  not as hardcore as I do. Well, they were high school girls with a proper
  social life, after all.

  Ever since that moment, they had treated me like a real friend. Uta and Mikoto
  seemed to already knew each other from middle school, yet they allowed me to
  enter their group as if I had already earned my place. We went on a "light
  after-school meal", as Mikoto liked to put it, and explored school club
  options together. Even though at the end me and Uta remained unchanged in our
  decision not to join any club, it was still a fun experience. I would never
  have known what clubs were there in my high school if I did not go, y'know.

  Today, since Mikoto had practice with her club, there were just me and Uta.
  We went on a karaoke session along with about ten of our classmates, an
  experience I had not gone through in my long middle school life. It was a
  blast! Even a first-timer like me, filled with nerves and anxiety, would like
  to go again with everyone, but since it was quite of a draining experience,
  too.

  Through these limited experiences with my two new friends, I think they were
  pretty good friends to me. I know my judgment might be biased since I had
  never had friends that close, but they had really treated me well, even though
  we had known each other for a few days.

  Take Mikoto, for example. She was the kind of athletic girl who tended to say
  anything that come to her mind. She tended to freeze up when things she
  cherished were at stake, like how our first interactions and her
  self-introduction to Setoguchi-senpai at the Tracks & Fields team went, which
  I thought was pretty cute. Even though those traits made her seem like an
  airheaded girl, she was surprising sharp at times. She was the one who first
  found out my love for idols, after all.

  Uta, on the other hand, seemed like a pretty nonchalant girl who tried to keep
  up her social appearance. She could communicate well with everyone, from girls
  befitting her social status to awkward people like me. However, the more I
  spent time with her, the more I found her perceptive. Today, she knew that it
  was my first time visiting a karaoke shop, so she really did try her best on
  encouraging me. If not for her, I would not have been able to sing a single
  song, honestly. Her good deeds could be her putting up a front, but I don't
  think that's worth all the efforts she was making.

  Overall, it has been a perfect high school debut for me. Seemingly too
  perfect, I think. It was as if God heard my prayers and decided to treat me
  better than like, the millions of people who actually need his help. I was not
  complaining, though.

  In religions, those who had been blessed by God had the duties to lead other
  people to peace and righteousness, like in Confucianism or Christianity.
  I don't think I'm a suitable guide, regardless. See, God, even with your help,
  I was being dragged by Mikoto and Uta all the time. I enjoyed the time with
  them, but well, I don't think I could be a leader in any way.

  I rolled around to face the wall next to my bed. The poster of Miyutan, my
  favorite _oshi_ for the moment, wobbles a bit due to my sudden motion. I
  instinctively raised my hand to keep it still, but my hand came short.

  Misuzu High School, the thing I once deemed to be far beyond my reach, was now
  the place I'm spending my next three years at.

  Friends with the same interests as me, I thought finding them would be
  something hard akin to finding a needle in a haystack, yet they showed up
  before my eyes without any efforts of my own.

  Maybe, in life, many hardships that seemed excruciatingly difficult to achieve
  could be finished in a miraculous night.

  So perhaps, even I could change, too.

  I recalled the past moments I spent with Uta and Mikoto. It was warm and
  fuzzy in my heart, yet it felt incomplete. They were my friends, but I could
  not chat with them freely. Even when I had nothing to hide.

  I was blessed with such great friends and all, yet I was asking for more. I
  wished that when morning come, I could walk to their homes early, and us three
  would go to school together. I wished that I could stay at school late until
  Mikoto finished her practice, then we could together go for a treat. More than
  anything, I wished to tell them how much I enjoyed spending time with them.

  Yet, my voice always came up short.

  Feeling too restless to fall asleep, I took out my phone to kill time. I
  clicked on the short video app, expecting to see a plethora of pointless
  trivia. The first video recommended to me was something I did not expect,
  nonetheless.

  _"Everyone wants their life to change, yet no one wants to make the change."_

  // spying allegations...
  A semi-inspirational video appeared. It seemed that the algorithm was again
  being experimented on, since I don't normally follow this type of content.
  However, that quote somehow hit the nail on the spot.

  I kept asking for things to change, kept wishing on things that I could
  totally do it myself.

  I questioned myself. What was the last time I actively was going out of my
  comfort zone? The only thing that came to mind was the first time I went to an
  actual idol concert without having my sister coming along. At first, it was
  scary, but in the end, I had a blast, and could freely cheer on the performer
  with 100\% of my energy.

  Since that day, I had been going to more and more concerts. Concerts with a
  ludicrously high ticket fee, check. Concerts that for some reason were
  organized at some prefecture 2 to 4 hours of train riding from Tokyo, check.
  Concerts that take place right in Shinjuku that somehow take an hour to
  enter the venue due to the sheer audience, also check. My extensive merch
  collection was also mostly goods that I collected from such trips, too.

  Since that day, I felt as if I _graduated_. No, not the _graduation_ in the
  idol sense, it's like I graduated from middle school to go to high school,
  that kinda stuff! My knowledge widened, and I started to become aware of more
  obscure idols, as well as many random trivia about the idol industry. Do you
  know that Cocona-chan had failed ten, yes, ten idol auditions before debut?
  That was a little secret that she revealed only to me at the meet and greet
  section.

  So maybe, this time too, I should try walking outside my comfort zone again.

  I briefly recalled Mikoto and Uta, as well as how they always cared about this
  plain-old me. I wanted to help them too, but I could never find the chance to.

  Filled with motivation, I abruptly stood up from my bed.

  // sparkle reference gg
  It's no longer an option I have to choose.

  It's my duty that must have been kept.

  My heart was filled with determination. Yes, I will draw the sword to kill
  this timid past self of mine, becoming someone that not only Uta and Mikoto,
  but I could even be proud of!

  Tomorrow, I will break the ice. I will not allow myself to stay silent when
  Uta and Mikoto are throwing banters. I will pick a side, no longer giving them
  the awkward silence like the last day.

  I swear to God! If you are listening, then please engrave these lines to your
  heart, and punish the humble me if I dare to go back on my words tomorrow.

  // ai koto4
  // LÁO VÃI L**
  // ĐCM THẰNG SÚC VẬT TÁC GIẢ
  I felt as if this burning and pounding heart of mine was beating faster than
  the metronome at a rock idol concert, and nothing, absolutely nothing, could
  ever stop it.

  Throwing my fists up and almost reached the ceiling, I felt a sudden vibration
  from the beddings. It was my phone, still looping the semi-inspirational video
  from earlier, with a new Mine notification.

  "Mikoto: Good evening, Mona-chan! Sorry for not messaging you sooner, I was
  so--- busy with club stuff. #emoji.hands #emoji.hands #emoji.hands Also how
  is karaoke today, did Uta do something horrible to you? I will teach her a
  lesson later!"

  I chuckled, then quickly sent her a reply,

  "Mona: Nice to meet you, too! #emoji.hand.wave Uta did not did anything bad to
  me at all! #emoji.face.smile.sweat"

  See, it was already an improvement! Past me would spend at least ten minutes
  debating on what to send Mikoto! I even used emojis this time, too.

  "Mikoto: Why so stiff, Mona? #emoji.face.cry #emoji.face.cry #emoji.face.cry
  You can just message me normally #emoji.face.cry #emoji.face.cry
  #emoji.face.cry"

  Oops, it seemed that my overconfidence had biten me in the ass. It seemed that
  my journey of self-transformation would take a lot more efforts than I
  anticipated, after all.
]
